<section class="mission-details">
	<div class="mission-intro">
		
		<a name="eztoc19726776_1" id="eztoc19726776_1"></a><h2><b>The mission</b></h2><p>The Earth Cloud Aerosol and Radiation Explorer (EarthCARE) satellite mission will advance our understanding of the role that clouds and aerosols play in reflecting incident solar radiation back out to space and trapping infrared radiation emitted from Earth’s surface.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="mission-data">
		
		<a name="eztoc19727799_1" id="eztoc19727799_1"></a><h2><b>The launch</b></h2><p>
<b>Date:&nbsp;</b>2024<br />
<b>Site</b><b>:</b> Vandenberg, California, US<br /><b>Rocket:</b> SpaceX Falcon 9</p>
	</div>
		<div class="mission-logo">
		<img src="/var/esa/storage/images/applications/observing_the_earth/futureeo/earthcare/19728822-17-eng-GB/EarthCARE_pillars.png"> 
	</div>
	</section>

<section class="mission-stats connecting-benefiting">
	
		
		
<ul>

<li><b>4</b> instruments</li>

<li><b>21 sq m</b> solar panel</li>

<li><b>393 km</b> altitude</li>

<li><b>25 days</b> repeat cycle</li>

</ul>

	
